Entecavir is an oral antiviral drug used in the treatment of hepatitis B infection. It is marketed under the trade name Baraclude (BMS).&#13;
&#13;
Entecavir is a guanine analogue that inhibits all three steps in the viral replication process

Efavirenz (brand names Sustiva&#174; and Stocrin&#174;) is a non-nucleoside reverse transcriptase inhibitor (NNRTI) and is used as part of highly active antiretroviral therapy (HAART) for the treatment of a human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) type 1.&#13;
&#13;
For HIV infection that has not previously been treated
